From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Klaus Zimmermann <klaus_zimmermann@gmx.de>
Date: Fri, 12 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Honor the CMAKE_ARGS environment variable in setup.py's cmake
 invocation

PyTorch's setup.py builds its own cmake command line in
tools/setup_helpers/cmake.py and otherwise ignores the CMAKE_ARGS
environment variable. conda-forge (like scikit-build-core) delivers the
whole cross-compilation toolchain -- CMAKE_SYSTEM_NAME, CMAKE_OSX_SYSROOT,
the cross binutils, etc. -- as -D flags in CMAKE_ARGS, and these must reach
cmake *before* project() runs its compiler detection.

Since PR #177640 moved environment-variable forwarding into
cmake/EnvVarForwarding.cmake, which is include()d after project(), nothing
puts CMAKE_ARGS on the command line in time for the setup.py build path, so
cross-compilation breaks. Honor CMAKE_ARGS here -- the convention used by
scikit-build-core and conda-forge -- so it lands on the command line before
project(), matching how every other cmake invocation in the recipe already
consumes it. Split on spaces to match how the rest of the conda build
consumes CMAKE_ARGS.

CMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX is filtered out: cmake.py sets it itself just above
(the build installs into its own tree, not the user's prefix), so -- like
scikit-build-core, which filters the options it manages -- CMAKE_ARGS is not
allowed to override it.

Signed-off-by: Klaus Zimmermann <klaus_zimmermann@gmx.de>
---
 tools/setup_helpers/cmake.py | 12 ++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 12 insertions(+)

diff --git a/tools/setup_helpers/cmake.py b/tools/setup_helpers/cmake.py
index 1234567..89abcde 100644
--- a/tools/setup_helpers/cmake.py
+++ b/tools/setup_helpers/cmake.py
@@ -301,5 +301,17 @@
         # Reference:
         # 1. https://cmake.org/cmake/help/latest/manual/cmake.1.html#synopsis
         # 2. https://stackoverflow.com/a/27169347
+        # conda-forge: PyTorch's setup.py builds its own cmake command line and
+        # ignores $CMAKE_ARGS. Honor it (the scikit-build-core / conda-forge
+        # convention) so conda's cross toolchain reaches cmake before project().
+        # Skip CMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX, set just above -- like scikit-build-core,
+        # filter the options the build script manages so CMAKE_ARGS can't
+        # override them.
+        args.extend(
+            arg
+            for arg in os.environ.get("CMAKE_ARGS", "").split()
+            if not arg.startswith("-DCMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX=")
+        )
+
         args.append(base_dir)
         self.run(args, env=my_env)
